data.description: Nestled in the charming town of Holly Springs this picturesque 3-bedroom, 2-bathroom home situated on .54 acres offers an ideal blend of comfort and elegance. As you approach, you're greeted by a long, paved driveway leading to a spacious two-door, two-car garage. The home's inviting exterior is matched by its thoughtfully designed interior, which features a welcoming foyer adorned with durable luxury vinyl plank flooring that extends through the main living areas. To the left of the foyer lies a formal dining room, which boasts stylish wainscoting and coffered ceilings, perfect for hosting dinner parties or enjoying family meals. Straight ahead, the open living area unfolds with its impressive, vaulted ceilings and exposed beams. At the heart of this space, a cozy fireplace stands as the focal point, offering warmth and ambiance. The eat-in kitchen offers a breakfast area perfect for casual dining. The kitchen is a chef's delight with a stone backsplash, elegant granite countertops, white cabinets, a pantry and a suite of matching stainless-steel appliances, including dual wall ovens. The breakfast bar provides additional seating, making it a great spot for morning coffee or entertaining guests. The primary suite is a haven of relaxation with its plush carpeting, tray ceilings, and expansive walk-in closet complete with built-in shelving. A sitting area off the primary suite adds an extra touch of luxury. The attached primary bathroom is a true spa-like retreat, featuring a soaking tub, walk-in shower, dual vanities, and a private restroom. The home's two additional bedrooms, also carpeted, share a full-sized bathroom and offer comfortable accommodation for guests. Additionally, there is a large, carpeted room over the garage, perfect for a home office, gym, or media room. There is a 24x24 garage utility room for added convenience. Step outside onto your screened-in back porch overlooking a concrete patio - an ideal setting for relaxing or entertaining. The large, fenced-in yard, backed by mature trees, ensures privacy and safety for guests and pets.    Buyer to receive a Lender Credit UP TO $1500 if closing with Preferred Lender Tanya Brinson/Movement Mortgage.    Buyer must be Prequalified with Preferred Lender and loan to meet all lending guidelines.    Preferred closing attorney, Whitaker & Hamer - Clayton
